HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 325
BY REPRESENTATIVE BAYHAM
COMMENDATIONS: Commemorates Sail 250 New Orleans and the arrival of the tall
ships of the world in New Orleans from May 28 through June 1, 2026, in honor of
the two hundred fiftieth anniversary of the United States of America
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commemorate Sail 250 New Orleans and the arrival of the tall ships of the world in New
3 Orleans from May 28 through June 1, 2026, in honor of the two hundred fiftieth
4 anniversary of the United States of America.
5 WHEREAS, New Orleans will be the first stop as America welcomes the tall ships
6 of the world to the Port of New Orleans for a nationwide celebration of the two hundred
7 fiftieth anniversary of the United States of America; and
8 WHEREAS, from May 28 through June 1, 2026, the city will celebrate the
9 Sestercentennial of America with the largest-ever flotilla of tall ships from around the world;
10 and
11 WHEREAS, Sail 250 New Orleans will bring a majestic nautical spectacle to the
12 historic Mississippi River and host a diverse array of events, festivities, and celebrations
13 across the region to educate, entertain, and engage audiences from communities across the
14 country; and
15 WHEREAS, the Port of New Orleans will welcome twelve tall ships and naval
16 vessels from Argentina, Chile, Colombia, the Netherlands, Peru, Sweden, the United
17 Kingdom, the United States, and Uruguay; and
18 WHEREAS, the U.S. Coast Guard Cutter Eagle is regarded as "America's Tall Ship"
19 and is homeported in New London, Connecticut; it is a two hundred ninety-five-foot, three-
20 masted barque that carries twenty-two thousand square feet of sail and has a core crew of
