1 and fastest tall ships, serves as a training vessel for the Argentine Navy, and has sailed over
2 eight hundred thousand nautical miles and visited five hundred ports in more than sixty
3 countries; and
4 WHEREAS, USS Kearsage is a versatile amphibious assault ship designed to project
5 power from sea to shore and carries Marines, aircraft, and landing craft in a single integrated
6 platform; the ship has a flight deck that resembles a small aircraft carrier and a floodable
7 well deck for amphibious operations, and it serves as a floating hub for rapid-response
8 military and humanitarian missions worldwide; and
9 WHEREAS, USS Farragut is a multi-mission guided missile destroyer built to defend
10 against air, surface, and subsurface threats while operating independently or as a part of a
11 carrier strike group; the ship is equipped with the Aegis Combat System and a versatile array
12 of missiles and sensors, and it delivers precision, speed, and adaptability across modern
13 naval operations; and
14 WHEREAS, USCGC Mohawk is a medium endurance cutter built for long-range
15 patrols, specialization in law enforcement, search and rescue, and maritime security
16 missions; the ship features a balanced mix of endurance, speed, and seakeeping and serves
17 as a reliable workhorse on extended operations across coastal and international waters; and
18 WHEREAS, HMS Trent is a modern offshore patrol vessel built for persistent global
19 presence, conducting maritime security, counter-smuggling, and patrol missions far from
20 home waters; the ship is designed for efficiency and endurance and combines a relatively
21 small crew with advanced sensors and a flexible mission deck to operate independently for
22 extended deployments; and
23 WHEREAS, it is with great pride that the state of Louisiana recognizes the tall ships
24 and naval vessels of the world during the landmark celebration of the two hundred fiftieth
25 anniversary of the nation.
26 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
27 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commemorate Sail 250 New Orleans and the arrival
28 of the tall ships of the world in New Orleans from May 28 through June 1, 2026, in honor
29 of the two hundred fiftieth anniversary of the United States of America and does hereby
30 encourage citizens to join in the celebration of the storied maritime history of the nation.
